Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{2} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss sweet potatoes and mushrooms with half the @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}
(you'll use the rest later), a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}.

> For 4 servings, spread sweet potatoes and mushrooms out across entire sheet.

Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper.

> For 4, add bell peppers to a second sheet; roast sweet potatoes and mushrooms
> on top rack and bell peppers on middle rack.

Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (the veggies will finish cooking in step 5).

== Pickled Cucumbers ==

While veggies roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine juice from three lime wedges
(six for 4 servings), @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4), a splash of @water{},
and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Stir in cucumbers. Set aside to quick-pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready
to serve.

== Creamy Sriracha Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon},
and as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like.

> Start with half the Sriracha, then taste and add more from there if you like
> things spicy.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Once veggies have roasted 15 minutes, remove sheet from oven.

> For 4 servings, remove sheet with sweet potatoes and mushrooms; leave bell
> peppers roasting.

Using a #spatula{}, toss sweet potatoes and mushrooms with half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}
(save the rest for serving), remaining hoisin, and a pinch of lime zest.

Return to top rack until veggies are tender and glaze is tacky, ~{5-8%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with roasted veggie mixture. Top with
@crispy fried onions{1}, pickled cucumbers (draining first), and remaining
@sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}.

Drizzle with as much creamy Sriracha sauce as you like. Serve with any remaining
lime wedges on the side.